From 279208efba39b21853ea984baf24c37774d13c54 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Claude Opus 4.8" <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 02:57:09 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 16/16] /saf VFS branch + file-op hooks under CONFIG_ANDROID
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wire the /saf pseudo-paths into cmus's file ops, consuming the SAF RPC
transport from the previous patch. A /saf/... path looks like a normal
absolute path, so cmus's char* machinery (dirname/join, browser .., the
cache/library/playlist key) is untouched; only the sites that actually
touch the filesystem branch on is_saf_path().

- OPEN (input.c open_file_locked): a /saf input's fd comes from saf_open()
  (a real, seekable bridge fd passed over SCM_RIGHTS) instead of open().
- Reopen seam (ip_reopen_path): for a /saf input, return /proc/self/fd/N
  — an independent, seekable re-open of the already-open bridge fd — so
  the ex-open-by-path plugins (ffmpeg/mp4/aac + mad/wavpack tag readers)
  work with no per-plugin surgery. A non-NULL sidecar (wavpack's .wvc)
  issues a fresh bridge OPEN and returns its /proc/self/fd; that extra fd
  rides input_plugin_data.saf_extra_fd and is closed with the input in
  ip_reset().
- LIST (load_dir): dir_open() fetches a whole /saf child listing in one
  saf_list() RPC and dir_read() walks it in place of readdir(), so a
  library import is one round-trip per directory, not per entry. The app
  supplies the ".." entry. browser.c's do_browser_load() also skips its
  pre-dir_open stat() for /saf (which would ENOENT) and treats the path
  as a directory.
- STAT (cache.c freshness): both sites that stat ti->filename go through
  saf_stat() for a /saf path — file_get_mtime at first-cache and the
  cache_refresh (update-cache / Refresh metadata) mtime compare. Using
  the STAT RPC's mtime at both keeps the compare stable; a -SAF_ENOENT
  drops a vanished track while a transient bridge error leaves it be.

Gated on CONFIG_ANDROID and inert unless $CMUS_ANDROID_SAF_SOCKET is set;
direct-mode POSIX paths never reach these branches.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

diff --git a/android.c b/android.c
index 3056ca1..4004945 100644
--- a/android.c
+++ b/android.c
@@ -998,6 +998,28 @@ int saf_enabled(void)
 	return saf_reader_started;
 }
 
+/*
+ * Path-segment test: exactly "/saf" or a "/saf/..." prefix. A substring
+ * match would wrongly catch a real ".../saffron", so the segment must end
+ * at a '/' or the string's end.
+ */
+int is_saf_path(const char *path)
+{
+	return path[0] == '/' && path[1] == 's' && path[2] == 'a' &&
+		path[3] == 'f' && (path[4] == '\0' || path[4] == '/');
+}
+
+/* map a negative -SAF_E* code to an errno for the bridged file-op sites */
+int saf_errno(int rc)
+{
+	switch (-rc) {
+	case SAF_ENOENT:	return ENOENT;
+	case SAF_ENOTSEEK:	return ESPIPE;
+	case SAF_ECANCELED:	return ECANCELED;
+	default:		return EIO;
+	}
+}
+
 /* little-endian encode into a request frame */
 static void saf_put_u16(struct gbuf *b, uint16_t v)
 {
diff --git a/android.h b/android.h
index af425ba..d8313f0 100644
--- a/android.h
+++ b/android.h
@@ -100,8 +100,24 @@ int saf_stat(const char *path, struct saf_stat *st);
 int saf_list(const char *path, struct saf_dirent **entries, size_t *count);
 void saf_list_free(struct saf_dirent *entries, size_t count);
 
+/*
+ * /saf VFS branch (patch 0016).
+ *
+ * is_saf_path() is a path-segment test: it matches exactly "/saf" or a
+ * "/saf/" prefix, never a substring (".../saffron" does not match), so the
+ * file-op sites can cheaply route a pseudo-path to the bridge above.
+ * saf_errno() maps a negative -SAF_E* code (as returned by saf_open/
+ * saf_stat/saf_list) to an errno value, so a bridged site can set errno and
+ * report a normal I/O failure; -SAF_ENOENT maps to ENOENT, which the cache
+ * refresh uses to tell a vanished file from a transient bridge error.
+ */
+int is_saf_path(const char *path);
+int saf_errno(int rc);
+
 #else
 
+#define is_saf_path(path) 0
+
 #define android_fd -1
 #define android_client_fd -1
 #define android_init() { }
diff --git a/browser.c b/browser.c
index 238b396..78d6f39 100644
--- a/browser.c
+++ b/browser.c
@@ -25,6 +25,7 @@
 #include "misc.h"
 #include "options.h"
